{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/paper-review-resmlp","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"0060d8ed-e927-5c86-8336-b055753c508b","html":"<p><a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2105.03404\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Paper link</a></p>\n<p>Code available <a href=\"https://github.com/lucidrains/res-mlp-pytorch\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">here</a> </p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 960px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/6c554c04f5f345cf18df9ef51eaeea47/2a4bc/collage.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/6c554c04f5f345cf18df9ef51eaeea47/8ac56/collage.webp 240w,\n/static/6c554c04f5f345cf18df9ef51eaeea47/d3be9/collage.webp 480w,\n/static/6c554c04f5f345cf18df9ef51eaeea47/e46b2/collage.webp 960w,\n/static/6c554c04f5f345cf18df9ef51eaeea47/f992d/collage.webp 1440w,\n/static/6c554c04f5f345cf18df9ef51eaeea47/882b9/collage.webp 1920w,\n/static/6c554c04f5f345cf18df9ef51eaeea47/14846/collage.webp 3264w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/6c554c04f5f345cf18df9ef51eaeea47/8ff5a/collage.png 240w,\n/static/6c554c04f5f345cf18df9ef51eaeea47/e85cb/collage.png 480w,\n/static/6c554c04f5f345cf18df9ef51eaeea47/d9199/collage.png 960w,\n/static/6c554c04f5f345cf18df9ef51eaeea47/07a9c/collage.png 1440w,\n/static/6c554c04f5f345cf18df9ef51eaeea47/29114/collage.png 1920w,\n/static/6c554c04f5f345cf18df9ef51eaeea47/2a4bc/collage.png 3264w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/6c554c04f5f345cf18df9ef51eaeea47/d9199/collage.png\"\n            alt=\"collage\"\n            title=\"collage\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>In this paper, researchers from Facebook AI, Sorbonne University and INRIA present ResMLP, an architecture built entirely upon multi-layer percep-trons for image classification. It’s a residual network which that contains a linear layer in which patches\ninteract independently across channels and a two-layer feed-forward network in which channels interact independently per patch.\nWhen trained with modern training strategies it shows decent accuracy / complexity tradeoff on ImageNet.</p>\n<h2 id=\"method\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#method\" aria-label=\"method permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Method</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 886px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/6e2f675b996a63869b8263c9bc7625e4/cc155/fig_1.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 25.416666666666664%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/6e2f675b996a63869b8263c9bc7625e4/8ac56/fig_1.webp 240w,\n/static/6e2f675b996a63869b8263c9bc7625e4/d3be9/fig_1.webp 480w,\n/static/6e2f675b996a63869b8263c9bc7625e4/b4685/fig_1.webp 886w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 886px) 100vw, 886px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/6e2f675b996a63869b8263c9bc7625e4/8ff5a/fig_1.png 240w,\n/static/6e2f675b996a63869b8263c9bc7625e4/e85cb/fig_1.png 480w,\n/static/6e2f675b996a63869b8263c9bc7625e4/cc155/fig_1.png 886w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 886px) 100vw, 886px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/6e2f675b996a63869b8263c9bc7625e4/cc155/fig_1.png\"\n            alt=\"fig 1\"\n            title=\"fig 1\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h4 id=\"the-residual-multi-layer-perceptron\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#the-residual-multi-layer-perceptron\" aria-label=\"the residual multi layer perceptron permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>The Residual Multi-Layer Perceptron</h4>\n<p>Residual Multi-Layer Perceptron is a combination of linear and feedforward layers paralleled by a skip-connection.\nAuthors replace Layer Normalization with simple affine transformation because of sufficiently stable training. It’s used twice\nfor each block - as a pre-normalization and as a post-processing to replicate behaviour similar to the recent\nLayerScale which improves the optimization of deep transformers.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 341px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/3fc9d5cb56a29ef22ffe4898653ca91b/4c0ad/affine.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 12.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/3fc9d5cb56a29ef22ffe4898653ca91b/8ac56/affine.webp 240w,\n/static/3fc9d5cb56a29ef22ffe4898653ca91b/5af35/affine.webp 341w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 341px) 100vw, 341px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/3fc9d5cb56a29ef22ffe4898653ca91b/8ff5a/affine.png 240w,\n/static/3fc9d5cb56a29ef22ffe4898653ca91b/4c0ad/affine.png 341w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 341px) 100vw, 341px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/3fc9d5cb56a29ef22ffe4898653ca91b/4c0ad/affine.png\"\n            alt=\"affine\"\n            title=\"affine\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Also ReLU replaced by a GeLU function. Self-attention replaced by a linear interaction.\n<br><br>\nOverall structure of the perceptron</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 407px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/ed6def20c7b6415e0f833d50b90bb7b8/0ff56/mlp_block.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 20.833333333333336%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/ed6def20c7b6415e0f833d50b90bb7b8/8ac56/mlp_block.webp 240w,\n/static/ed6def20c7b6415e0f833d50b90bb7b8/c9427/mlp_block.webp 407w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 407px) 100vw, 407px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/ed6def20c7b6415e0f833d50b90bb7b8/8ff5a/mlp_block.png 240w,\n/static/ed6def20c7b6415e0f833d50b90bb7b8/0ff56/mlp_block.png 407w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 407px) 100vw, 407px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/ed6def20c7b6415e0f833d50b90bb7b8/0ff56/mlp_block.png\"\n            alt=\"mlp_block\"\n            title=\"mlp_block\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h4 id=\"overall-idea\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#overall-idea\" aria-label=\"overall idea permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Overall idea</h4>\n<ol>\n<li>Take <em>N x N</em> non-overlapping patches as input. </li>\n<li>Create a set of <em>N squared</em> d-dimensional embeddings.</li>\n<li>Feed embeddings to several Residual Multi-Layer Perceptron layers to produce a set of <em>N squared</em>.\nd-dimensional output embeddings.</li>\n<li>Average embeddings as a d-dimensional vector using average pooling or an alternative of class-attention introduced in CaiT paper.</li>\n<li>Feed obtained vector to a linear classifier.</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"experiments\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#experiments\" aria-label=\"experiments permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Experiments</h2>\n<p>Models were trained on the ImageNet-1K dataset.</p>\n<h4 id=\"imagenet-classification\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#imagenet-classification\" aria-label=\"imagenet classification permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>ImageNet classification</h4>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 926px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/a25ea6c544c228e620a79fc5e7fc920f/69476/experiments.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 90.41666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/a25ea6c544c228e620a79fc5e7fc920f/8ac56/experiments.webp 240w,\n/static/a25ea6c544c228e620a79fc5e7fc920f/d3be9/experiments.webp 480w,\n/static/a25ea6c544c228e620a79fc5e7fc920f/dafe9/experiments.webp 926w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 926px) 100vw, 926px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/a25ea6c544c228e620a79fc5e7fc920f/8ff5a/experiments.png 240w,\n/static/a25ea6c544c228e620a79fc5e7fc920f/e85cb/experiments.png 480w,\n/static/a25ea6c544c228e620a79fc5e7fc920f/69476/experiments.png 926w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 926px) 100vw, 926px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/a25ea6c544c228e620a79fc5e7fc920f/69476/experiments.png\"\n            alt=\"experiments\"\n            title=\"experiments\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h4 id=\"transfer-learning\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#transfer-learning\" aria-label=\"transfer learning permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Transfer learning</h4>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 874px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/ba26318d8be2498f1149758c2ea7dc56/30c92/transfer.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 37.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/ba26318d8be2498f1149758c2ea7dc56/8ac56/transfer.webp 240w,\n/static/ba26318d8be2498f1149758c2ea7dc56/d3be9/transfer.webp 480w,\n/static/ba26318d8be2498f1149758c2ea7dc56/02c22/transfer.webp 874w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 874px) 100vw, 874px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/ba26318d8be2498f1149758c2ea7dc56/8ff5a/transfer.png 240w,\n/static/ba26318d8be2498f1149758c2ea7dc56/e85cb/transfer.png 480w,\n/static/ba26318d8be2498f1149758c2ea7dc56/30c92/transfer.png 874w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 874px) 100vw, 874px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/ba26318d8be2498f1149758c2ea7dc56/30c92/transfer.png\"\n            alt=\"transfer\"\n            title=\"transfer\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Original paper have interesting ablation study which refers to communication with low-resolution\nconvolutions and normalization.</p>\n<h2 id=\"conclusion\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#conclusion\" aria-label=\"conclusion permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Conclusion</h2>\n<p>Authors pointed out that simple residual architecture combined with modern training strategy\ncan achieve high perfomance on image classification task. Work will contribute to understanding\nof designing networks without pyramidal structure adopted by most convolutional neural networks.</p>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/paper-review-resmlp","tagSlugs":["/tag/computer-vision/","/tag/image-classification/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2021-05-11T23:46:37.121Z","description":"My review of the paper ResMLP: Feedforward networks for image classification with data-efficient training","tags":["Computer Vision","Image Classification"],"title":"Paper Review: ResMLP: Feedforward networks for image classification with data-efficient training","socialImage":{"publicURL":"/static/6c554c04f5f345cf18df9ef51eaeea47/collage.png"}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/paper-review-resmlp"}},"staticQueryHashes":["251939775","401334301","825871152"]}